{
  "texts": [
    "For the study in this dissertation, the last tool was modified to return the SQL query even if it was incorrect.",
    "Clear Prompting addresses two problems: (1) the size of the database schema may exceed the prompt limit; (2) a prompt with too many tables and columns may confuse ChatGPT.",
    "Clear prompting then recalls relevant tables and columns (to the NL question) and adds them to the prompt, along with the schema.",
    "This component employs Self-Consistency (seen in Section 3.2.3.4), where the LLM generates multiple responses for a given task, clusters them with similar ones, and selects the most consistent response through a voting mechanism.",
    "Column recall is also a zero-shot prompt that instructs the LLM to: (1) recall columns; (2) rank all columns within each candidate table based on their relevance to the question; (3) give priority to columns that better match NL question words and foreign keys."
  ]
}